info: COUNTER: Counts the total characters in the webpage URL
COUNTER: Counts the number of numeric characters in the webpage URL
COUNTER: Counts the number of sensitive words
RATE: Counts the percentage of external hyperlinks in webpage HTML source code
RATE [0,1]: Counts the percentage of hyperlinks fields containing empty value
BINARY {0,1}: Checks if the most frequent domain name in HTML source code does not match the webpage URL domain name
BINARY {0,1}: Check if HTML source code contains the HTML “mailto” function.
~CATEGORICAL [-1,0,1]: Counts the percentage of external resource URLs in webpage HTML source code.
~CATEGORICAL: Counts percentage of meta, script and link tags containing external URL in the attributes.
CATEGORICAL: Counts the percentage of hyperlinks in HTML source code that uses different domain names, starts with “#”, or using “JavaScript ::void(0)”.
